# DaisyUI + Angular CDK + Tailwind CSS

## UI Stack

- **Components**: DaisyUI v4 (semantic CSS classes)
- **Behavior**: Angular CDK (overlays, a11y, drag-drop)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v3.4.x utilities
- **Icons**: `lucide-angular` (tree-shakeable, consistent)
- **NO Angular Material** — never import `@angular/material/*`

## Theming

Single-color generation via `generateCollaTheme(primaryHex)` in `tailwind.config.js`. Each colla defines only a primary hex; secondary, accent, and content colors are computed automatically.

```html
<html lang="ca" data-theme="colla-barcelona">
```

**No CSS custom properties** — all colors via DaisyUI tokens (`primary`, `base-100`, `base-content`, etc.). Never use `var(--colla-*)`.

## Responsive Design

- **Mobile-first**: base styles = mobile, `sm:` / `lg:` for larger
- **Layout**: top bar + tab-nav (no sidebar/drawer)
- **Tables**: horizontal scroll (`overflow-x-auto`) — never card-view duplicates
- **Forms**: `w-full sm:w-64` pattern for responsive widths

## DaisyUI Patterns

### Cards

```html
<div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-sm">
  <div class="card-body p-4">…</div>
</div>
```

Accent: `border-l-4 border-primary` on the card div.

### Modals

Use native `<dialog>` with `modal modal-open` + `modal-backdrop`:

```html
<dialog class="modal modal-open">
  <div class="modal-box">…</div>
  <div class="modal-backdrop" (click)="close()"></div>
</dialog>
```

### Badges

Semantic: `badge-success`, `badge-error`, `badge-warning`, `badge-info`, `badge-ghost`.
Dynamic color: `[style.backgroundColor]` + `[style.color]="getContrastColor(color)"`.

### Buttons

Size: `btn-sm` for actions inside cards/tables. `btn` for primary page actions.
Variants: `btn-primary`, `btn-outline`, `btn-ghost`, `btn-error`.

## Angular CDK

Use for complex behavior that DaisyUI can't handle:
- `@angular/cdk/overlay` — programmatic dropdowns/tooltips
- `@angular/cdk/a11y` — focus trapping in custom dialogs
- `@angular/cdk/drag-drop` — future pinyes canvas module

## Styling Rules

- All visual styling via DaisyUI semantic + Tailwind utilities
- **No `.scss` files** unless complex animations are needed
- No `@apply` — prefer inline classes
- Dynamic Tailwind classes: use static maps, never template literals
- UI text: always Catalan
